The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for computing various parameters related to minors in graphs. This falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of combinatorial techniques and Erdős-Pósa property suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS), graph theory (cs.GT), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
